Add and Format New Volume on Instance

1. Check available disks:
   lsblk
   (e.g., existing disk: vda, new volume: vdb)

2. Create partition on new volume:
   sudo cfdisk /dev/vdb
   - Select GPT if prompted
   - Create new partition, then Write and Quit

3. Format the new partition:
   sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/vdb1

4. (Optional) Mount the new partition:
   sudo mkdir /mnt/data
   sudo mount /dev/vdb1 /mnt/data

5. (Optional) Make the mount permanent:
   sudo blkid        # Get UUID of /dev/vdb1
   sudo nano /etc/fstab
   Add this line at the end:
   UUID=xxxx-xxxx  /mnt/data  ext4  defaults  0  2
